━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Working Together

If

A completes work in **10 days**

B completes work in **5 days**

One-Day Work

```text
A = 1/10

B = 1/5
```

Together

```text
1/10 + 1/5

=

1/10 + 2/10

=

3/10
```

They complete **3/10** of the work in one day.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Finding Total Days

Formula

```text
Days

=

1

────────────

One-Day Work Together
```

Example

Together they complete

```text
3/10
```

of the work in one day.

Days required

```text
1 ÷ (3/10)

=

10/3

=

3⅓ days
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Solved Example 1

A completes work in **6 days**

B completes work in **3 days**

### Step 1

```text
A = 1/6

B = 1/3
```

### Step 2

```text
1/6 + 1/3

=

1/6 + 2/6

=

3/6

=

1/2
```

### Step 3

```text
Days

=

1 ÷ (1/2)

=

2 Days
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Solved Example 2

A completes work in **12 days**

B completes work in **18 days**

### Step 1

```text
A = 1/12

B = 1/18
```

### Step 2

Take LCM of 12 and 18 = 36

```text
1/12 + 1/18

=

3/36 + 2/36

=

5/36
```

### Step 3

```text
Days

=

1 ÷ (5/36)

=

36/5

=

7 1/5 Days
```

✅ Final Answer:

```text
7 1/5 Days
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

