# ❌ Common Mistakes

## Mistake 1

Writing

```text
One-Day Work = Days
```

❌ Wrong

Correct

```text
One-Day Work = 1 / Days
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Mistake 2

Forgetting to take the reciprocal.

Example

```text
Together = 5/36
```

❌ Wrong

```text
5/36 Days
```

✅ Correct

```text
36/5 Days

=

7 1/5 Days
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Mistake 3

Adding fractions without taking LCM.

Always make the denominators the same before adding.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💡 Interview Questions

## Q1

If A completes a work in 20 days, what is A's one-day work?

**Answer**

```text
1/20
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Q2

How do you calculate work done together?

**Answer**

Add the one-day work of all persons.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Q3

How do you calculate total days?

**Answer**

Take the reciprocal of the combined one-day work.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Q4

What is the first step in every Time & Work problem?

**Answer**

Find the one-day work.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

